      <h1 class='title'>Departmental Expenditure</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 28 February 2003 vol 400 cc45-7WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_45ws' title='Col. 45WS &mdash; HC Deb 28 February 2003 vol 400 c45WS' name='column_45ws' href='#column_45ws' rel='bookmark'>45WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0400P2_20030228_CWS_11'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-charles-clarke' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0400P2_20030228_CWS_11' title='Link to this speech by Mr Charles Clarke' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-charles-clarke" title="Mr Charles Clarke">The Secretary of State for Education and Skills (Mr. Charles Clarke)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">This Written Statement explains the changes being proposed to the Department for Education and Skills' Departmental Expenditure Limit (DEL) (including the Office for Her Majesty's Chief Inspector of Schools (OFSTED) which has a separate Estimate), which subject to Parliamentary approval of</p><p>
          <table>
          <tr>
          <td></td>
